#14501
The Zoo Atrium~
   The zoo's main thoroughfare houses large clay planters adorning each wall
containing large green leaved plants with various blooms.  At each corner sits
a bench for resting while purusing the zoo's offerings.  Sounds of animals
drift into this central area and the myriad of smells come together to create
a deeply wild smell here.  In the center of this room sits a dark wooden
platform made for speaking above a crowd.  The ceiling is intricately made of
thin brass bars that are anchored at the top of each wall and come together in
a dome shape to form a circle in the center.  This celing allows rain and
sunshine to nourish the lush plants within the atrium.  Drains in the floor
allow the excessive rain to exit without flooding the atrium.  
~
