#14503
Malchor's Monkey World~
   This exhibit was designed to replicate a jungle environment geared toward
the canopies of trees.  The stone ceiling has an iron-barred opening almost
the size of the room to allow natural sunlight and weather to nourish the
plants.  There are natural trees planted into the dirt and brush floor here,
but also carefully cut ropes, vines and large branches anchored about to allow
for climbing.  A small platform in the nortwest corner of the room holds
several overturned bowls and the remains of some fruit that must have been
placed there by one of the animal handlers.  
~
