#14504
Lyratha's House of Lizards~
   This exhibit is designed to simulate and focus on a forest floor.  The air
in here is humid, and dead leaves and branches line the floor.  A large log
sits in the northeast corner of the small room providing shelter for the
miniature forest's inhabitants.  The door of the exhibit is wood-framed, with
multiple layers of woven fabric that prevents the escape of the lizards.  
Light is emitted from several torches that are brightly burning from their
places on the stone wall.  They illuminate several hand-made trees made of
real wood, twigs, and some green fabric cut into the shape of leaves.  
~
