Pizentios' Pachyderm Playground~
   This exhibit is designed to replicate a grassland environment.  The hard,
dusty ground sprouts tufts of grass all over in various stages of growth.  A
large, tiny-leaved tree droops over a pool of clean water in the southeast
corner.  Large pillars of wood block the entrance, preventing the creatures
escape, except for an opening large enough for a person.  Light spills in from
the large opening in the stone ceiling and sounds of birds can be heard from
within the tree.  
