#14516
Treatment Bay~
   This large open space is brightly lit by torches that line the southern and
western walls.  In the center of the room, a wide rectangular table sits with
iron rings lining each side.  Several chains linked to the iron rings seem to be
made for restraint of animals being treated.  In the northeast corner a large
iron table is lined with neatly organized medical tools and a wooden
shelf above it contains dozens of dark bottles.  A pungent odor is present
here and seems to be emanating from a pen to the north.  
