#14524
Quarantine Room~
   The large iron-barred door leads into an expansive room that lay in a state of
destruction.  Windows to the north and east cast bright sunlight into the
room, illuminating wooden splinters that litter the stone floor.  What looks
to be the base of the container on iron wheels still remains rooted in the center
of the stone floor.  The unmistakably animal scent is stronger here and has a
sickly, sweet quality to it.  In the northwest corner, an iron-legged wooden
table sits with various papers and journals neatly situated upon it.  
~
