E
splinters wood wheel base cage~
   The remaining pieces of this cage can be summed up to an iron and wooden
plank base that sits on four heavy iron wheels.  The size indicates that the
base was a part of a cage large enough to hold a monstrously large animal.  
The wooden planks that presumably made up the walls of the cage lie scattered
about the room and almost seem as if the whole thing exploded outward.
~
E
leather bound journal log~
   The words quarantine log are embossed on the front of this leather-bound
journal.  It is open to an entry that records a date and time of intake of a
creature called an Arctodus Sinus.  It goes on to describe various unusual
behaviors of the animal that include, excessive aggression, increased
respirations, and a permanent dilation of pupils.  In the last entry, it is
stated that the Arctodus Sinus is exhibiting aggression even up to the
creatures own peril and seems to elevate when any other living creature is
present.  It goes on to indicate that the author will be requesting approval to
euthanize the animal from the Zoomaster.  
~
E
iron legged table~
   This oak-topped table has seen years of use exhibited by gouges and stains
that have become a permanent part of its surface.  Upon it lie several bound
leather journals and scattered papers.  One of these leather-bound journals
lie open with a fountain pen open beside it.  
~
S
