#14526
The Zaivrag Exhibit~
   This room was expertly designed to mimic a mountainous terrain.  The floor
slopes upward at a sharp angle to the northwest corner and is made of sheared
pieces of slate rock and limestone.  Scraggly trees have been placed here, but
have since died, giving the landscape a desolate quality.  The air is fresh
here, likely the result of the extremely large opening in the ceiling crossed
with thin iron bars.  There are boulders throughout the exhibit providing
plenty of places for a creature to hide.  
~
