#14527
The Maaralis Biome~
   Gray and green moss hangs from thick branches that are anchored from wall
to wall.  Theis moss hangs in large clumps of scraggly green and gray hues.  
The branches are anchored a low points on each wall inside the room and are
anchored on the other end at a peak in the wall opposite, creating a dome.  
The ground is a damp, bouncy surface that extends from wall to wall.  The
sounds of insects can be heard chirping from inside the clumps of moss.  At
the southern end of the exhibit, a large wooden platform stands holding
several bowls containing water and some sort of food.  
~
