#14529
The Metallic Slug Exhibit~
   The entrance to this cave is a man-made archway of stone that seems to
glitter from the light shining in from an iron-barred hole cut out of the
ceiling.  The walls are made of the same glittering stone, but made smooth as
to cover the joints and seams.  A slimy, wetness covers the walls in trails
that seem to cross over themselves repeatedly.  The light from above
illuminates a pile of wet sludge emitting a foul odor in the northen curve of
the cave and a shallow, dark pond sits in the western curve.  
~
