#14530
The Exhibit of the Torewe~
   The walls of this exhibit have been covered by bark to add to the
forest-like atmosphere that was intended.  The ground is a combination of soil
and dead leaves that rustle underfoot.  Several different species of small
trees are planted throughout the exhibit.  The trees are bushy and have smell
yellow to green leaves that peak in number at their rounded tops.  Light comes
in from above through several iron-barred holes designed to allow the sunlight
to nourish the living exhibit.  Birds flit through the trees and sounds of the
zoo filter in from outside the exhibit.  
~
