#14531
The Nark Exhibit~
   A desert landscape is the clear goal of the creator of this exhibit.  
Amber sand spans the entire floor of the pen with stone walls and iron barred
windows confining the occupant within.  In the northeast corner of the room,
dark stone boulders have been stacked on top of one another to create a
cave-like structure with an extremely large opening in the front.  In the
southeast corner, nearest the iron barred doorway, a murky and stagnant pond
sits with flies buzzing over the surface.  The remains of a small animal rot
right outside the entrance to the cave.  
~
